<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,266,1860]" pageId="6" pageNumber="44">
<taxonomicName box="[198,432,1685,1710]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Pavonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Malvales" pageId="6" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="exasperata">
<emphasis box="[198,432,1685,1710]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="44">Pavonia exasperata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Krapovickas (1977: 318)" authorityName="Krapovickas" authorityPageNumber="318" authorityYear="1977" box="[591,992,1685,1711]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Pavonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Malvales" pageId="6" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="friesii">
<emphasis box="[591,689,1685,1710]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="44">P. friesii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Krapovickas, A." box="[698,992,1685,1711]" pageId="6" pageNumber="44" pagination="307 - 322" refId="ref4090" refString="Krapovickas, A. (1977) Sinopsis de la seccion Lebretonia del genero Pavonia (Malvaceae). Trabal. XXVI Congr. [Bras.] Nac. Bot. 1975, pp. 307 - 322." type="journal article" year="1977">Krapovickas (1977: 318)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Krapovickas (1977: 320)" authorityName="Krapovickas" authorityPageNumber="320" authorityYear="1977" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Pavonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Malvales" pageId="6" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis box="[1052,1194,1685,1710]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="44">P. orientalis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Krapovickas, A." pageId="6" pageNumber="44" pagination="307 - 322" refId="ref4090" refString="Krapovickas, A. (1977) Sinopsis de la seccion Lebretonia del genero Pavonia (Malvaceae). Trabal. XXVI Congr. [Bras.] Nac. Bot. 1975, pp. 307 - 322." type="journal article" year="1977">Krapovickas (1977: 320)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
due to its similar narrow epicalyx bracts, usually sagittate leaf blades, and white or pale pink petals with basally vinaceous center and veins. However, 
<taxonomicName box="[713,876,1760,1785]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Pavonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Malvales" pageId="6" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="exasperata">
<emphasis box="[713,876,1760,1785]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="44">P. exasperata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from these species mainly in its larger mericarps with two to three lateral tubercles at each side of the median nerve. In addition, this species may present slightly lobate leaf blades, especially in basal leaves.
</paragraph>
